From: Kairo Authors <kairo@research>
Date: Wed Jun 24 20:00:00 2026 +0000
Subject: [RFC/POC] 0029: KV residency heatmap scaffold

RFC/POC — Not for LKML submission.

Add a conceptual KV-cache residency heatmap that tracks per-region
access frequency, recency, and classification (hot/warm/cold/evictable/
protected).  The heatmap enables the kernel storage stack to make
informed caching and eviction decisions based on actual I/O patterns.

AI runtimes (vLLM, TensorRT-LLM, SGLang) exhibit strong temporal
locality in KV-cache access — some regions are decode-hot (frequently
read), some are warm (periodic prefetch), and many are cold or
evictable (stale session data).  Today this access dynamics is
invisible to the kernel.

This patch adds:

  enum kairo_kv_heat_class
    KAIRO_KV_HEAT_UNKNOWN
    KAIRO_KV_HEAT_HOT
    KAIRO_KV_HEAT_WARM
    KAIRO_KV_HEAT_COLD
    KAIRO_KV_HEAT_EVICTABLE
    KAIRO_KV_HEAT_PROTECTED

  struct kairo_kv_heatmap_entry
    valid, region_id, model_id, session_id, cache_pool_id,
    placement_group, start_sector, nr_sectors, heat_class,
    decode_reads, prefetch_reads, prefill_writes, evictions,
    last_decode_ns, last_prefetch_ns, last_write_ns,
    recompute_ok, persistent, protected_region, heat_score

  struct kairo_kv_heatmap
    enabled, nr_regions, decay_interval_ns, last_decay_ns,
    regions[KAIRO_KV_HEATMAP_MAX_REGIONS], hits, misses,
    updates, decays, evictable_regions, protected_regions

  KAIRO_KV_HEATMAP_MAX_REGIONS fixed at 1024 (RFC/POC only).

Conceptual helpers (all static inline __maybe_unused no-ops):

  kairo_kv_heatmap_lookup(struct request *rq)
  kairo_kv_heatmap_account_decode(struct request *rq)
  kairo_kv_heatmap_account_prefetch(struct request *rq)
  kairo_kv_heatmap_account_write(struct request *rq)
  kairo_kv_heatmap_account_eviction(struct request *rq)
  kairo_kv_heatmap_decay(struct kairo_kv_heatmap *map, u64 now_ns)
  kairo_kv_heatmap_classify(const struct kairo_kv_heatmap_entry *entry)
  kairo_kv_heatmap_region_evictable(
      const struct kairo_kv_heatmap_entry *entry)

Heat scoring policy (RFC heuristic):

   decode read hit             +20
   prefetch read hit           +5
   prefill write               +2
   eviction candidate check    -5
   age decay                   -10 per interval
   recompute_ok                lowers protection
   persistent                  strong protection

Classification thresholds:

   score >= 100       HOT
   score >= 40        WARM
   score >= 1         COLD
   score <= 0 and recompute_ok  EVICTABLE
   persistent         PROTECTED

Integration points (documented in comments):

   Stage 17: KV region hints provide the region topology.
   Stage 18: eviction policy consumes heat class.
   Stage 13/14: decode latency feedback influences decay rate.
   Stage 12/15: fairness weights influence per-session heat.
   Stage 7: backend mapping uses heat for placement hints.

Sysfs counters (defined but not wired to any kobject):

   kairo_kv_heatmap_hits
   kairo_kv_heatmap_misses
   kairo_kv_heatmap_updates
   kairo_kv_heatmap_decays
   kairo_kv_heatmap_hot_regions
   kairo_kv_heatmap_warm_regions
   kairo_kv_heatmap_cold_regions
   kairo_kv_heatmap_evictable_regions
   kairo_kv_heatmap_protected_regions

CONCEPTUAL-HOOK: No dispatch-path integration, no sysfs registration,
no runtime heatmap state.  The heatmap model is defined for RFC review
and benchmark-driven policy exploration.

LINUX-6.8-CHECK:
  block/blk-mq.c:          blk_mq_rq_ctx_init, blk_mq_dispatch_rq
  block/blk-core.c:        generic_make_request
  include/linux/blk-mq.h:  struct request (no kairo_hints field)

Signed-off-by: Kairo Authors <kairo@research>
